column2: Sunny- small ripples- 1" rain overnight- fair amount of suspended algae- surface water temp 79 F.
Partly sunny- light chop- 80s- suspended algae- surface water temp 80 F.
Sunny- 80 F- suspended algae- surface water temp 81 F.  Lake level: very high
Calm- partly cloudy- 80 F- suspended algae- several rainy days during week.
Light breeze- sunny- 70*- .3" rain overnight- suspended algae- surface temp 76 F.
Light E breeze- sunny- 70 F- .2" rain overnight- suspended algae- smaller particles this week- surface temp 76 F.
Light S breeze- sunny 60 F- suspended algae- surface temp 70 F.
West wind- sunny with the temperature at 70- no rain- very small particles of suspended algae- surface water temperature is 67 degrees.
Calm and sunny- the temperature is 60 degrees F weather and rain every day- algae amount is down- and the surface temperature is 65 degrees F.
Calm and sunny- this is 50 degree F weather with the water surface temperature at 58 degrees F.
Light breeze- sunny- the temperature is 40 degree F weather and the surface water temperature is 51 degrees F.
Calm and sunny- the air temperature is 50 degrees F- the water is 51 degrees F- and no algae visible.
Light west breeze- medium chop- air temperature is 80 degrees F- 0.9" of rain in previous week- some algae- and the surface temperature is 77 degrees F.
Light breeze- hazy- 90 degrees F air temperature- no rain in past week- some algae- and surface water temperature is 80 degrees F.
Strong wind- sunny- the temperature is 80 degrees F- 2.1" rain previous week- some algae- and the surface temperature is 75 degrees F.
Calm- partly sunny- 80 degrees F air temperature- 2.9" rain during previous week- algae- and surface temperature is 85 degrees F.
Sunny- S breeze- 90 F air- no rain last week- lots of algae- surface temp 85 F.
Sunny- S breeze- 70 F air temp.- lots of algae- 1.5" of rain last week- surface temp. 78 F.
Calm- sunny- 70 F weather- .1" rain in past week- abundant particles of algae- surface temp. 73 F.
Windy- sunny- 60 F weather- rained 1.85" in last week- fine particles of algae- surface temp. 64 F.
Sunny- W breeze- 40 F weather- rained 1.7" last 3 days- surface temp. 47 F.
Sunny- light breeze- 40 F weather- no rain in last week- surface temp. 43 F.
Sunny- light breeze- air temp. 50 F- .35" of precipitation last week- surface temp. 43 F.
Sunny- light breeze- 40 F weather- no rain in last week- surface temp. 41 F.
Partly cloudy- strong S breeze- 80 F- no rain since snow melt- ice off 4/12/88.
Sunny- S breeze- 70 F- 0.1" rain last week- suspended algae- very fine particles- surface temp. 77 F.
Sunny- light N breeze- 80 F weather for past week- .4" of rain in last week- fine particles of suspended algae- surface temp. 77 F.
Sunny and calm- .9" rain since last reading- suspended algae- water 76 F.
Sunny- calm- 80 F- suspended algae- water 81 F.
Sunny- bright- N wind- 90 F- 2.45" rain last week suspended algae- surface temp 82 F.
Sunny- light N breeze- 80 F- .2" rain last week- suspended algae- surface temp. 82 F.
Sunny- N breeze- 90 F- abundant fine suspended algae- surface temp 80 F.
Sunny- S wind- 90 F- 2.35" rain last week- fine suspended.  Algae abundant- surface 81 F.
Sunny- light S breeze- 70 F- 2.5" rain- lots of suspended. algae- surface temp. 70 F.
Sunny- light N breeze- + 0 F- 0.9" rain- suspended. algae abundant- water 63 F.
Sunny- S breeze- 50 F- 6.1" rain since last reading- suspended algae- water 49 F.
Sunny- light breeze- 40 F- 2.4" rain since last reading- some suspended algae.
Strong S wind- sunny- 80 F- some suspended algae- 1.75 in. rain past week.
Sunny- calm- 90 F- surface temperature. 78 F- some suspended algae- 1 in. rain last week.
Sunny- light N breeze- 80 F- some suspended algae- water surface temp. 77 F- 1.25" rain last week.
Sunny- S breeze- 90 F- no rain past week- suspended algae- surface temp. 79 F.
Sunny- NW breeze- 70 F- trace of rain past week- abundant algae- surface temp. 76 F.
Sunny- calm- 80 F- 2.35" rain past week- abundant suspended algae- surface temperature 75 F.
Sunny- N breeze- 80 F- 2.9" rain last week- abundant suspended algae- water 76 F.
Sunny- W breeze- 60 F- 2.8 in. rain since 8/22- water 67 F- lots of fine algae- coarse zooplankton.
Sunny- 60 F- W breeze- less algae- .5 in. rain since last reading- water 58 F.
Sunny- N breeze- air 50 F- water 51 F- .35" rain since last reading- coarse zooplankton common.
Sunny- S breeze- air 50 F- water 50 F- fine zooplankton- no rain since last.
Sunny- S breeze- air 70 F- water 41 F- no suspended particles- 1.55" rain since last.
Ice off; no secchi reading taken.
Sunny- N breeze- air 70 F- water 72 F- some suspended algae- 1.6" rain in past week.
Sunny- S breeze- suspended algae in deep water- surface algae in shallow water- water 77 F.
Sunny- S breeze- 80 F- 5.4" rain since last- water 76 F- lots of fine suspended particles.
Sunny- S breeze- large particles suspended algae- see Haberkorn Bay comments.
Sunny- S breeze- 80 F- mod. suspended algae- water 73 F- 1.3" rain since last reading.
Sunny- south wind- abundant fine particles- algae suspended.
Sunny and calm- abundant suspended algae.
Bright hazy sun- south breeze- small amount of suspended algae.
Bright sun- S breeze- more suspended algae- .85" rain in past week- air temps in last week 70's.
Bright sun- S wind- abundant suspended algae- .45" rain in the past week- 80 degree air temp for past week.
Bright sun- south breeze- abundant suspended algae- 0.1" of rain in the past week- 80 degrees temps the past week.  Sheets of methane  bubbles coming up in mucky bays- 1st time I noticed this year.
Bright sun- north breeze- very small amount of suspended fine sized algae- 0.6" of rain in the past week- 40 degrees temps in the past week.
Bright sun- south wind- large suspended particles in Haberkorn Bay- 0.65" of precipitation in the past week- 50 degrees temps in the past week.
South breeze- sunny- fine and coarse particles suspended in the water.
Light haze- sunny- south breeze- abundant fine algae particles suspended in water.
LAKE HAS NO APPARENT ODOR AT SAMPLING TIME
Light overcast- not much suspended algae- south breeze. ice off 4-18-95.
Haberkorn Bay 11'.  76 degrees F- full sun- NW breeze- some suspended algae- rain 1.75" 6/17/95-7/7/95.
Northwest breeze- sunny- 75 degrees.  3.25" precipitation from 6/18/95 to 7/16/95.
Northwest breeze- 100% sun- abundant algae suspended in water- 77 degrees.  6.95" precipitation from 7/17/95 to 8/19/95.
Southwest. breeze- 100% sun- 43 degrees.  12.5" precipitation from 8/20/95 to 10/25/95.
87 degrees- south breeze- abundant suspended algae- 3.5" precipitation from 5/14/96-6/14/96. Ice out 4/30/96.
Full sun- 84 degrees- south breeze- abundant algae suspended in lake.
100% sun- south breeze- abundant suspended algae- Department of Natural Resources bands 3 osprey chicks- remove 2 for shipment to state of Kansas.
100% sun- south breeze- abundant suspended algae- lots of zooplankton.
Light overcast- south breeze- abundant suspended algae.
67 degrees. Partly cloudy- S breeze- lots of tree pollen suspended in water.
84 degrees. Cloudy to full sun- S breeze- abundant suspended algae.  7" precipitation from 6/18/97 to 7/25/97.
Sunny- 55 degree air temp- light SW breeze- abundant particles of algae- no zooplankton present- saw 2 loons and 2 gulls flying over the lake- 1.3" rain from 9/26/97 to 10/16/97.
82 degrees light breeze.  Suspended algae. Osprey feeds young. Water has slight odor at 60 and 70 feet.
87 degrees light breeze.  Lots of algae.  Saw 2 loons osprey.  The loon chicks have disappeared.
83 degrees light S breeze.  Some suspended algae.  Loon chicks okay.  Water has slight odor at 50- 60 and 70 feet.
86 degrees SW breeze.  Small particles of suspended algae.  Loon family broken up young are alone.
62 degrees SE breeze water very clear.  Trees in full color.  Water has slight odor and 50 60 and 70 feet.
61 F- strong NE breeze- 50% sun- moderate amount suspended algae- 2 adult loons with 2 chicks about 10 days old in outlet bay.
82 F- NW breeze- 100$ sun- moderate amount suspended algae- saw family of 4 otters- 2 loon chicks are fine- osprey chicks disappeared- eagles perch on osprey nest.
62 F. Calm. 100% sun.  Tremendous amount of very small suspended algae.  Loon chicks gone (training flight ) white oak - purple.  Tamarack - yellow.
A pair of loons on big bar.
Color strip 6. 86 degrees F.- sunny and calm.  Lots of suspended algae. 3 loons feeding- osprey use platform for resting and feeding.
One loon east of the big island- one osprey resting on the platform.

Color strip 6. 63 degrees F.- S breeze- sunny- some thin clouds. Lots of suspended algae- 0 zooplankton- 5 loons (2 adults) feeding on lake- 8 loons fly over lake heading south. 1 eagle on osprey platform.  Strong odor to water at 40- 50- 60- and 70 feet.
Abundant suspended algae. North breeze. 100% sun- air temp 67.4 deg F. Saw loon east of Big Island
Abundant suspended algae. Light haze. Air temp 73 deg F. 1 loon in bay. 3 adult ospreys near platform and chicks in nest.
Abundant suspended algae. Sunny- air temp 92 deg F. 1 loon chick- 3 single loons fishing. 3 osprey chicks on platform- adults drive off eagles.
Abundant suspended algae. Some zooplankton. No clouds. Air temp 94 deg F and calm. 1 Loon at deep hole. 3 osprey chicks out of nest- 1 perched on a dead branch.
Lots of algae. Full sun. 1 osprey- 1 loon flying over lake.
Lots of algae and zooplankton. Redtail hawk in Haberkorn Bay. Osprey on the platform. Cormorant by Long Island. Air temp 66 deg F.
Full sun- 72 deg F. Loon chick E. of Big Bay. 1 osprey soaring around lake. Painted turtle on log in Musky Bay. 1 Kingfisher.
Lots of suspended matter from turnover.  Full sun- 57 deg F.  Loon chick near Deep Hole.  6 gulls on lake.
Buzzards and eagles soar over lake. No clouds- 80 deg F- south breeze. Lots of yellow tree pollen (pine) on the lake surface. 1 loon on Big Bar- osprey on platform.
Temp at 1 ft = 71.4. 1 osprey chick on platform. Basswood blooming.
Puffy clouds- 80 deg F. North breeze. 1 loon near manicure island. Osprey chick on platform is getting feathers. Lots of suspended algae. Chick near adult size and losing it's fuzz.
Temp at 1 ft. = 78.6 F. Light south breeze. Lots of suspended algae.
Air temp 80 deg F.- strong NW breeze- sunny to bright days. 2 loons- osprey chick flies- acorns drop- butternut leaves yellow- squirrels eat butternuts.
Temp at 1 ft. = 78.4 F. Air temp 80 F- osprey chick begs for food on platform.
Temp at 1 ft. = 69.8 F. Air temp 65 F. Osprey on platform- eagle in outlet bay.
Air temp 64 deg F- calm- no clouds. 2 osprey- 2 gulls- 2 geese- acorns continue to drop. Some basswood- birch- ash leaves yellow.
Air temp 70 F- no clouds- calm. Leaves 100% color. See cormorant and gull- osprey chick is gone.
Water became murky after a large rain (4" in 24hrs).
